Another family has been ambushed and killed in KwaZulu-Natal. On Thursday, a family was accosted by unknown gunmen who fired multiple shots at the five members of the family aged between 19 and 34 in Nteke area, Mariannhill. Captain Nqobile Gwala said, “Four of the family members died at the scene and the other victim died in hospital on arrival,” Mariannhill police have opened a docket with five counts of murder and it has been transferred to the Provincial Organised Crime Task Team for investigation. The motive of the attack is under investigation. She added, “such family attacks cannot be tolerated, we will work around the clock to solve these cases and send the killers behind bars so that it can be a lesson to others who still think that they can get away with the crime”. Three days ago, a similar attack was committed at Ematimatolo area were eight women from one family were brutally murdered. It is said that unknown assassin stormed in two family homes few meters apart and opened fire leaving seven females dead. The killers also doused with petrol the houses with the deceased and set them alight. -TNA Reporter   